The Senate has given a nod to the decision of its committee on power to allow individuals and other entities with proven capacity to generate, distribute and supply electricity, to do so. The Upper Chamber of the National Assembly in a debate on the report which was laid during plenary by the Committee Chairman, Senator Gabriel Suswam, noted the importance of having a robust power sector for the country. It said that concerted efforts must be made to ensure that the new legislation liberalises the sector further to among others, allow for increased power generation, distribution and supply to enhance economic growth. Details Later……..